<br>
Kanebic Blacknight <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/8/01 10:23:13 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When is Vox Raid?</span><hr size=1> Here's how to read the Vox rotation and try to get an idea of when the raid will be. <br>
<br>
Currently the CoG is up 3rd for Vox. <br>
Vox(5/4): Ash(1), AoVB(1), FoF/CoG, SB,FA, LC, CGoF, Arm(2),Max(2), LD, Tris/Aargh/EdG<br>
<br>
Now, Vox will spawn today (5/<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  with the patch. Which means Ashborne alliance will go after her tonight (5/<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . If they fail, Alliance of Valiant Blades will go tomorrow night (5/9), or if Ashborne passes, AoVB will go tonight (5/<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Then if AoVB fails on 5/9, we'll be up the next night, 5/10 (or if Ashborne passed, and AoVB failed, we'd be up 5/9). Now, if Ashborne succeeds, Vox will spawn again in 7-9 days (or next server downage), which would put her spawning May 15th-17th. Which would put AoVB up for her on one of those days, (15th-17th), and if they fail, we'd be up the next night. Or if they pass we'd be up that night. If they succeed, add another 7-9 days after they succeeded and CoG would be up on that day (from the 22nd - 26th). So it's kind of hard to predict when we'll fight Vox for sure, unless she's killed less than 7 days before a patch. Which is why raids are so hard to pin down. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukanebic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kanebic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 7:17:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> OK! OK! My head is spinning<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I see its very complicated and hard to predict. I just wanted to know if we were going to get a shot at Vox in the near future. Thanks for the info. Let me go back and study my Algebra probabilities so I can keep up on the math<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kanebic Blacknight<br>
44th Paladin of Tunare<br>
Protector of the Weak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatrizspiritscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatriz Spiritscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Disciple</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 8:32:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> And the number that follows each spot on the rotation denotes....?  Number of attempts they get? <p><hr>
Zatriz Spiritscale<br>
Channeler of the Scaled Mystics<br>
Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 8:37:25 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> No, the number indicates number of failed raids since their last success. 2 or 3 failures or passes in a row and you sit out on 1 complete rotation. This is to keep the rotation from being cluttered with people who are unable to take the mobs down in a timely fashion.<br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatrizspiritscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatriz Spiritscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Disciple</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 9:13:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> Oh ok.  And here is a question I am not sure anyone can answer.  We (coolective guilds that participate in the rotation) have this nice rotation set up with rules about when you have to take you attempt on the dragon, how many attempts you get, and what happens if you can not suddenly take the dragon down.  But what happens when some outside guild jumps in and takes down the dragon?<br>
<br>
Does the KGC have any real authority?  The question might seem like heresy, but it is just curiousity.  I swear.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><hr>
Zatriz Spiritscale<br>
Channeler of the Scaled Mystics<br>
Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugruz2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gruz2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 9:34:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> Ash Did not take down the dragon yesterday.....so AoVB is up i doubt that raid will fail..............<br>
<br>
Gruz<br>
51Reaver<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Disciple</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 10:21:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> Thnx Gruz, we'll start getting ready<br>
<br>
Lagdalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatrizspiritscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatriz Spiritscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Disciple</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 10:36:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> So the CoG is looking at a Vox raid on the 15th-17th, unless AoVB fails or passes tonight.  Wish we had a better way of knowing for sure, because weeknights are tough for me.  If I had a couple days notice, I could schedule work around it, but I guess we have to get along as best as possible.<br>
<br>
Which brings up another question.  Vox spawned right after the patch.  Is the guild/alliance up for their turn &quot;forced&quot; to go the evening of her spawning?  Or could they wait for the weekend? <p><hr>
Zatriz Spiritscale<br>
Channeler of the Scaled Mystics<br>
Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Disciple</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 11:24:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> from the time that a dragon is known to be up you have aprox 24 hrs local time to the raid commander to kill him/her. If you are going to pass you post that as soon as possible as to give the next group as much time as possible to muster together. We are on MST and since most dont know the conversion we go by central for everyone else's ease.<br>
<br>
Lagdalen Tarcho <br>
lvl 51 Elementalist Officer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/9/01 12:46:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> Flarren MST is 1 hour behind CST, so 8 pm CST is 7 pm MST. <br>
<br>
If the dragon spawns AFTER 10 pm local time (i.e. CST for the CoG), you don't have to kill the dragon until the next day. Similarly, if the server goes down and doesn't come back until after 5 pm local time (again CST), you don't have to take the dragon the night it spawns (this is in case of late patches) but can wait until another night. <br>
<br>
If the target spawns the night before a patch (as all targets come up after a patch) and the guild that is up for the target is not able to make it OR pull off a switch with someone else in the rotation (yes you can swap turns in the rotation), the target can be declared Free for All and killed by a guild not up for the target. Doesn't happen very often. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugruz2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gruz2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/10/01 8:53:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> AoVB did take down Vox yesterday........<br>
<br>
CoG up next week.......<br>
<br>
Gruz <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showMessage?topicID=109.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showMessage?topicID=105.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=114.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.threadControl?topicID=114.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=114.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=114.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub6.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="councilofguildsgeneral">General<option value="councilofguildscouncildiscussions">Council Discussions<option value="councilofguildsevents">Events<option value="councilofguildscogplanesraidschedule">CoG Planes Raid Schedule<option value="councilofguildsfrm8">CoG Dragon Raids<option value="councilofguildsguildwars">Guildwars<option value="councilofguildshelpitemswanted">KCoG Bazaar<option value="councilofguildsintroduceyourguild">Introduce Your Guild<option value="councilofguild